-- Ambac says raises $1.5 billion from equity offering
-- 
-- Fri Mar 7, 2008 4:29am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/03/07/businesspro-ambac-stock-dc-idUSWEN438220080307

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Bond insurer Ambac Financial Group 
ABK.N said on Friday it has raised $1.5 billion of shares and 
convertibles in a bid to protect the company from ratings cuts. 

  Ambac said it priced a $1.155 billion public offering of 
171.1 million shares of common stock at $6.75 per share and 
granted the underwriters a 30-day option to purchase up to an 
additional 25.7 million shares to cover overallotments.  Ambac also said it has priced its $250 million public 
offering of 5 million equity units, with a stated amount of $50 
per unit.  (Reporting by  Yinka Adegoke ; Editing by Erica Billingham)